  "description": {
    "zh": "啊是的，正当我说到“常见武器类型”时，在俄罗斯AK就像长在树上一样。我真的需要多说 here 吗？当然不！当然，你可以拿着清单，我付钱给你不是让你首先去搞清楚你的任务是什么，那我成什么人了？总之，你看起来你的耳朵可以再听一个故事，好吧。\n\n我的表兄，他给我提供某些东西出去打猎，你可能已经知道也可能不知道，他后来成了一名枪匠。他只改装AK型步枪，我是说“只”。他几乎建造了这些枪所有可能的配置，枪管长度、口径、枪托类型，真的是一切。他的梦想是开自己的枪店来出售他的畸形作品，不幸的是对他来说从未成功，幸运的是对我们的眼睛……无意冒犯他，但有些枪看起来像被屠宰过。但过了一段时间，他确实受雇于KIBA Arms，对他来说是好事。\n\n遗憾的是，当所有事情开始在塔科夫这里发生时，我就再也没有他的消息了。别给我那种表情，你指望到处都有 happy end 吗？现在走吧。",
    "en": "Ah yes, right as I was speaking about \"common type of weapon\", It's like the AK grows on trees in russia. Do I really need to say much here? Of course not! Sure, you can have the list, I'm not paying you to figure out what your task is in the first place, who would I be? Anyway, you look like your ears could use another story, fine.\n\nMy cousin who supplied me with certain stuff to go out hunting, you may or may not know that already, he became a gunsmith, eventually. He only worked on AK-type rifles, and I mean \"only\". He pretty much built every possible configuration of these guns, barrel length, caliber, stock type, everything really. His dream was opening his own gun store to sell his abominations, unfortunately for him that never worked out, fortunately for our eyes... No offense to him, but some of these guns looked butchered. But after some time he did manage to get employed at KIBA Arms, good for him.\n\nSadly I never heard from him ever again when all the things started to happen here in Tarkov. Don't give me that look, you expect a happy end everywhere don't you? Now go."
  },
